2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 24
BY SENATOR STINE
COMMENDATIONS. Commends the Louisiana Endowment for the Humanities and
celebrates the 2026 Bright Lights Awards Honorees.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend the Louisiana Endowment for the Humanities and to recognize and celebrate
3 the 2026 Bright Lights Awards Honorees for their outstanding contribution to the
4 cultural and educational fabric of Louisiana.
5 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Endowment for the Humanities (LEH) has served the
6 people of Louisiana for fifty-five years by promoting education, preserving history, and
7 enriching public life through the humanities; and
8 WHEREAS, LEH's mission to foster learning, literacy, and a deeper understanding
9 of Louisiana's diverse people and stories has empowered generations of Louisiana families,
10 educators, and lifelong learners; and
11 WHEREAS, each year, LEH hosts the Bright Lights Awards Dinner to honor
12 individuals and organizations whose work exemplifies the values of the humanities and
13 whose contributions meaningfully preserve and celebrate Louisiana's cultural identity; and
14 WHEREAS, the 2026 Bright Lights honorees have made significant and lasting
15 impacts on Louisiana's cultural, educational, and historical landscape through their
16 exceptional work and dedication to the humanities; and
17 WHEREAS, the 2026 honorees include:
18 • Michael Doucet, recipient of the Humanist of the Year award, in recognition
