1 of his extraordinary contributions to Cajun music, language, and culture as the founder of
2 the internationally acclaimed band BeauSoleil;
3 • Pam Atchison, named Champion of Culture, for her remarkable tenure as
4 executive director of the Shreveport Regional Arts Council for thirty-eight years;
5 • The RosaMary Foundation and the Keller Family Foundation, recipients of
6 the Chair's Award for Institutional Support, for each contributing more than twenty-five
7 years of support for the humanities in Louisiana;
8 • Kevin Rabalais, named Documentary Photographer of the Year, for his
9 extensive body of work documenting the everyday lives, traditions, and landscapes of
10 Louisiana;
11 • Don Marshall, recipient of the Lifetime Contributions to the Humanities
12 award, for his career and leadership supporting and uplifting the arts community in New
13 Orleans;
14 • Debra Jo Hailey, recipient of the Light Up for Literacy award, for her
15 lifelong dedication to improving literacy across Louisiana through family literacy festivals
16 and educational outreach;
17 •Thomas Patterson, recipient of Humanities Book of the Year for American
18 Populist: Huey Long of Louisiana, for his vital contributions to historical scholarship on
19 Louisiana's storied governor;
20 •Sascha Just, honored for Humanities Documentary Film of the Year for What
21 We Can Know About Edmond and Basile, a film exploring the lives and musical legacies of
22 19th-century Creole composers; and
23 •The Historic New Orleans Collection, honored for Museum Exhibition of
24 the Year for Captive State, Louisiana and the Making of Mass Incarceration, an exhibition
25 that brought to life the historical connections between slavery and mass incarceration; and
26 WHEREAS, these honorees contribute to the illumination of Louisiana's rich
27 heritage, serve as inspiration to future generations, and embody the spirit of excellence in
28 service to the people and the stories of this great state.
29 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
30 does hereby commend the Louisiana Endowment for the Humanities for its invaluable
